  "page": {
    "documentTitle": "是與應當的鴻溝 | Concept Reading Lab",
    "bodyClass": "knowledge-page knowledge-is-ought-gap",
    "heroHtml": "<div class=\"hero-inner\">\n  <div>\n    <p class=\"kicker\">Knowledge Study / facts / norms / reasoning</p>\n    <h1>是與應當的鴻溝</h1>\n    <p class=\"topic-subtitle\">Is-Ought Gap</p>\n    <p class=\"thesis\">知道世界現在是怎樣，並不會自動告訴你世界應該怎樣；從事實跳到規範，中間總得補上價值、目的或原則。</p>\n    <div class=\"hero-prompt\">\n      <strong>Read For</strong>\n      <p>這一頁要把『現況如此』和『所以應該如此』拆開，因為很多論證看似在陳述事實，其實中間偷帶了價值判斷卻沒說明。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <aside class=\"hero-note\" aria-label=\"主題資訊\">\n    <dl class=\"lexical-meta lexical-meta--knowledge\" aria-label=\"主題摘要\">\n      <div>\n        <dt>主題類型</dt>\n        <dd>哲學原則 / 規範推論</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>核心問題</dt>\n        <dd>Descriptive facts alone do not automatically yield normative conclusions</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>主要判準</dt>\n        <dd>描述命題、規範命題、隱含價值、推論完整度</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>讀完產出</dt>\n        <dd>能更清楚分辨一段說法裡，哪些是描述世界，哪些是在引入價值與規範</dd>\n      </div>\n    </dl>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-map\" aria-label=\"閱讀結構示意\">\n      <span>事實</span>\n      <span>價值</span>\n      <span>跳躍</span>\n    </div>\n  </aside>\n</div>",
    "mainHtml": "<aside class=\"compass\" aria-label=\"頁內導覽\">\n  <span>Reading Path</span>\n  <a href=\"#core\">讀法總覽</a>\n  <a href=\"#setup\">問題設定</a>\n  <a href=\"#lenses\">判準透鏡</a>\n  <a href=\"#psychology\">心理連結</a>\n  <a href=\"#applications\">現實映射</a>\n  <a href=\"#misreadings\">誤讀校正</a>\n  <a href=\"#questions\">延伸提問</a>\n  <a href=\"#sources\">來源</a>\n</aside>\n\n<article class=\"article\">\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"core\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Orientation</p>\n      <h2>事實可以告訴你地形，卻不會自己告訴你該往哪裡走</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">是與應當的鴻溝提醒我們：規範結論需要的不只是真假，還需要價值方向。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"core-card\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Core Tension</p>\n      <p>若忽略這條鴻溝，論證會看起來更自然；但也更容易把價值選擇偽裝成純客觀結論。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"principle-strip\" aria-label=\"本頁讀法\">\n      <div>\n        <span>01</span>\n        <strong>先把描述和規範分開</strong>\n        <p>『這件事常發生』和『這件事正當』是不同命題。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>02</span>\n        <strong>再找中間缺的價值前提</strong>\n        <p>要從是到應當，必須補上你在保什麼。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>03</span>\n        <strong>最後讓價值顯性化</strong>\n        <p>把隱含前提講出來，爭論才比較有機會對到真正分歧點。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"setup\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Setup</p>\n      <h2>從一句聽起來像事實推理、其實中間省了價值前提的話開始</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這個原則在倫理討論、政策提案與組織文化辯論裡特別重要。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"definition-grid\">\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>最小劇情</strong>\n        <p>有人說『市場本來就這樣競爭，所以我們就應該接受這種制度』；事實描述與規範認可其實已經被直接接在一起。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>真正難點</strong>\n        <p>很多跳躍不是惡意，而是價值前提在說話的人心裡已經太理所當然。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"concept-flow\" aria-label=\"問題展開\">\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">先陳述現況或事實</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">省略價值前提</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">直接跳到規範結論</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"paradox-frame\">\n      <strong>Key Point</strong>\n      <p>是與應當的鴻溝不是要你停止做規範判斷，而是要你把規範判斷需要的前提說出來。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"lenses\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Lenses</p>\n      <h2>四個看規範跳躍的角度</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">只要聽到有人從『就是這樣』直接跳到『所以應該這樣』，就值得停一下。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"lens-grid\">\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>事實是什麼</strong>\n        <p>說話者真的只在描述現況嗎？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>應當是什麼</strong>\n        <p>他最後推的規範結論是什麼？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>缺失前提</strong>\n        <p>中間還需要哪條價值原則或目標才推得過去？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>爭論位置</strong>\n        <p>真正不同意的，是事實判斷還是價值排序？</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"table-wrap\">\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>說法</th>\n            <th>隱含跳躍</th>\n            <th>應該補上的東西</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td>大家都這樣做</td>\n            <td>所以這樣做合理</td>\n            <td>從普遍到正當的價值前提</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>自然本來如此</td>\n            <td>所以應順其自然</td>\n            <td>自然性不等於規範正當</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>效率最高</td>\n            <td>所以應無條件採用</td>\n            <td>是否還有公平、安全等其他價值</td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"psychology\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Psychology</p>\n      <h2>為什麼人很容易把事實講成規範</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">因為當某種價值已內化得很深時，它會被體驗成像世界本身的一部分。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>價值會隱形</strong>\n        <p>越理所當然的價值排序，越不容易被自覺成前提。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>事實語氣更有權威</strong>\n        <p>把規範說成現實必然，往往比直接說『我認為應該』更有壓迫力。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>省略前提很省力</strong>\n        <p>不用交代價值，就能讓推理看起來更乾淨更快。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"micro-note\">是與應當的鴻溝不是文字遊戲，而是防止價值偷渡成自然事實。</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"applications\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Applications</p>\n      <h2>把價值前提帶回提案與文化討論</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">對工程與組織來說，很多『這不是理所當然嗎』的規則，其實都站在某種未說明的價值排序上。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>流程設計</strong>\n        <p>說『這流程最有效率，所以一定要用』時，其實已經預設效率比彈性更重要。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>產品策略</strong>\n        <p>以使用者常這樣做為由直接正當化產品方向，常會忽略我們是否應該強化那種行為。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>文化論述</strong>\n        <p>把現有團隊風格當成應然標準，很容易壓掉替代價值。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\">\n      <li>當論證從事實直接跳到規範時，補問一句『中間靠的是哪個價值前提』通常很關鍵。</li>\n      <li>價值前提說出來之後，很多表面上的事實爭論其實會轉成更誠實的價值排序討論。</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"misreadings\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Misreadings</p>\n      <h2>三個常見誤讀</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">是與應當的鴻溝不是說事實對規範沒用，而是說它們中間不能自動省略前提。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"collocation-list\" aria-label=\"常見誤讀\">\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>事實和規範完全無關</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>不是。事實能約束可行性，但不會自己生成價值。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>所以所有規範都是主觀的</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>不是。只是規範需要明說其所站的價值與原則。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>這只在哲學課才有</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>政策、流程、產品與文化討論天天都在碰。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"questions\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Questions</p>\n      <h2>這句『所以應該』，中間靠的是哪一條沒說出的價值</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">下面兩個問題很適合放在規範性提案前。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"prompt-grid\">\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>如果只接受事實描述，不接受那條隱含價值，結論還站得住嗎</strong>\n        <p>這能幫你把跳躍照亮。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>我們真正不同意的，是現況判斷還是價值排序</strong>\n        <p>很多混戰會在這一步變清楚。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"template-note\">\n      <strong>延伸路線</strong>\n      <p>延伸閱讀可接 Hume, naturalistic fallacy 與 moral reasoning。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"sources\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Sources</p>\n      <h2>來源與整理方式</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這一頁以 is-ought gap 為主，再把概念帶回政策、產品與組織規範討論。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"source-grid\">\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>主概念</strong>\n        <p>Is–ought problem 條目整理了從描述命題跳到規範命題的哲學問題。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Is%E2%80%93ought_problem\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Is-Ought Problem</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>相鄰概念</strong>\n        <p>Naturalistic fallacy 可作為對照，理解把自然或既有狀態當成正當性的風險。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naturalistic_fallacy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Naturalistic Fallacy</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>人物背景</strong>\n        <p>David Hume 的相關條目有助於理解這個問題在哲學史中的來源。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Hume\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">David Hume</a>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"reference-box\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"section-label\">Reference</p>\n        <h2>下一步</h2>\n        <p>讀完後可以找一段你最近聽到的『所以應該』論述，試著把中間缺失的價值前提補出來。</p>\n      </div>\n      <a class=\"reference-link\" href=\"../knowledge-topic-template.html\">打開模板</a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</article>"
  }
}
